Summary of Entity Connections and Flow:

Patient Registration → User Entity → Patient Entity: Patient registers, creates User and Patient accounts.

Patient Sign-In → User Entity: Patient signs in using User credentials.

Doctor Manual Addition → User Entity → Doctor Entity: Admin adds Doctor, creating User and Doctor accounts.

Doctor Sign-In → User Entity: Doctor signs in using User credentials.

Appointment Booking → Appointment Entity → Patient Entity + Doctor Entity: Patient books an Appointment with a Doctor.

Consultation → Consultation Record Entity → Appointment Entity + Patient Entity + Doctor Entity: Doctor creates Consultation Record after Appointment.

Bill Generation → Bill Entity → Consultation Record Entity: Bill is created based on Consultation Record.

Payment → Payment Entity → Bill Entity: Patient pays the Bill, Payment is recorded, and Bill status is updated to Paid.

Inventory Update → Prescription Entity → Inventory Entity: Prescription creates medication records, and Inventory is updated.

Patient and Doctor Interaction → Patient Entity + Doctor Entity: Patient and Doctor can view their respective data post-consultation.
